reviews.review_text:
Thank you       Thank you, Mike Lai for showing some common sense and not dicing Good Lovin' up into three separate tracks!

      Where did the idea originate that the existence of a drum solo meant a song was to be corrupted into three separate tracks? And some have gone further - every jam or evoking of another melody gets it's own track. Where will it end? Every chord change becomes a new track?
